Lesufi and Premier David Makhura have officially opened the Nomzamo Madikizela Mandela Primary School in Soweto today. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says his department has committed to opening a new school every month in the province this year.Lesufi and Premier David Makhura officially opened the Nomzamo Madikizela Mandela Primary School in Braamfischerville in Soweto on Wednesday morning.#BacktoschoolGP BacktoschoolGP Gauteng Premier David Makhura visits a grade R class at the newly constructed Bramfischerville Primary. pic.twitter.com/lTgewRDW9eThe newly built school has state-of-the-art equipment and uses paperless technology.Lesufi has officially handed over the keys of this school to its principal.The MEC says this is the first of many school s government plans to open in the province this year. Just a kilometre away from here, we are preparing to open another school. He says this school has taken in 1,300 of the 40,000 pupils who are yet to be placed in schools. Today from that list we are taking 1,300 learners here at Nomzamo Madikizela Mandela. The MEC says his department is also prioritising pupils with special needs and plans to build eight schools for pupils with disabilities this year.(Edited by Neo Koza )